,"Enlargement of labia majora and minora","Reduction in vaginal length","Loss of vaginal rugae"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring puberty, \u003Cstrong\u003Eenlargement of the labia majora and minora\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to the influence of increasing oestrogen levels. The labia becomes more prominent and develops increased pigmentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThinning of vaginal mucosa\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur during puberty; instead, the vaginal mucosa thickens and becomes cornified. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased vaginal acidity\u003C/strong\u003E is also incorrect as vaginal pH becomes more acidic during puberty due to increased glycogen production and colonisation by lactobacilli. \u003Cstrong\u003EReduction in vaginal length\u003C/strong\u003E is the opposite of what happens, as the vagina lengthens and widens during puberty. \u003Cstrong\u003ELoss of vaginal rugae\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur; vaginal rugae become more prominent during puberty.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese changes are driven primarily by increasing oestrogen levels and prepare the reproductive tract for sexual maturity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["During female puberty, the vaginal mucosa thickens and becomes cornified due to increased oestrogen levels.","The labia majora and minora enlarge and become more pigmented during puberty.","Vaginal pH becomes more acidic during puberty due to increased glycogen production and bacterial colonisation."],"references":["Kline MW, Blaney SM, Giardino AP, Orange JS, Penny DJ, Schutze GE, et al. Rudolph\u0027s Pediatrics, 23rd Edition. McGraw Hill Professional; 2018."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96323"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16273"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96323","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/ap